WEBVTT

00:09.442 --> 00:12.570
<i>FRANKIE:
Some days, from start to finish, just blow.</i>

00:12.746 --> 00:15.476
I'm never doing that again.

00:15.648 --> 00:17.138
What?

00:17.317 --> 00:19.615
- Mother's Day?
- Yeah, Mother's Day.

00:19.786 --> 00:22.584
- It should be outlawed.
- What? You don't mean that.

00:22.756 --> 00:25.589
The kids made breakfast.
You went to your mom's. It was good.

00:25.759 --> 00:28.319
I think you're confusing Mother's Day
with Father's Day.

00:28.495 --> 00:32.430
They are nothing alike.
Were you not here this morning?

00:35.168 --> 00:38.001
SUE: Axl, get out here!
Mom's food is getting cold!

00:38.171 --> 00:40.765
AXL: So? She feeds us cold food.
Now let me sleep.

00:40.940 --> 00:43.067
BRICK:
I lost my present.

00:43.243 --> 00:46.337
SUE: Brick, you just had it.
What is wrong with you?

00:46.513 --> 00:48.606
BRICK:
They don't really know.

00:48.782 --> 00:50.841
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

00:53.353 --> 00:55.218
- Happy Mother's Day.
- Happy Mother's Day.

00:55.388 --> 00:58.152
Wow! What a surprise.

00:59.059 --> 01:02.119
Thanks. This looks yummy.

01:02.295 --> 01:06.425
God, it's too early.
You woke me up in the middle of my REM.

01:06.599 --> 01:10.228
Very dangerous time to wake someone up.
Could've killed me.

01:11.237 --> 01:13.102
[SUE YELLS]

01:13.273 --> 01:16.765
Axl, you're so stupid!
You've ruined everything!

01:16.943 --> 01:20.709
Oh, yeah, it's all my fault.
Blame everything on me. Classic.

01:20.880 --> 01:23.542
Hey, I'm not gonna put up with that crap
on Mother's Day.

01:23.716 --> 01:26.776
- Do I gotta bang some heads around here?
- It's fine, Mike, really.

01:26.953 --> 01:29.251
Everything's fine. See?

01:29.422 --> 01:31.014
Fine.

01:31.191 --> 01:33.284
- I made you something, Mom.
- Oh!

01:33.460 --> 01:37.089
A macaroni picture frame.

01:37.263 --> 01:39.959
That's great, Brick. I love it.

01:40.467 --> 01:43.527
And a card from Sue?
You guys are spoiling me.

01:43.703 --> 01:46.297
It's gonna be hard going back
to my regular old life.

01:49.409 --> 01:50.899
Oh, yeah. Right.

01:51.077 --> 01:53.705
Uh, I'm going with a verbal card this year.

01:53.880 --> 01:57.043
Dear Mom: You're my mom.
Pretty cool mom.

01:57.217 --> 02:00.618
Chick stuff here, feelings, whatever.
Love, Axl.

02:01.087 --> 02:04.454
So, Mom, what do you wanna do today?

02:04.624 --> 02:05.921
- Oh!
- My frame.

02:06.092 --> 02:08.151
Oh, it's fine. It'll be fine.

02:08.328 --> 02:10.056
Great. Now it looks thrown together.

02:10.229 --> 02:13.495
I'm trying to sleep here.
Have some respect for other people, people.

02:13.666 --> 02:16.658
<i>I'm gonna watch SportsCenter
and let you hang out with your kids.</i>

02:16.836 --> 02:18.497
It's your day.

02:20.006 --> 02:22.975
<i>FRANKIE: See, that's where Mother's Day
and Father's Day are different.</i>

02:23.143 --> 02:25.668
<i>On Father's Day, it really is his day.</i>

02:27.914 --> 02:29.575
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

02:33.853 --> 02:35.821
- Happy Father's Day.
- Happy Father's Day.

02:35.989 --> 02:38.082
I held them off as long as I could.

02:38.258 --> 02:41.318
SUE: We made all your favorites:
eggs, sausage, waffles.

02:41.494 --> 02:44.486
BRICK: And a mini-doughnut Dad
with bacon arms.

02:44.664 --> 02:46.928
Well, I'll eat him first. Thanks.

02:47.100 --> 02:50.536
This looks great.
You kids really know how to cook.

02:51.404 --> 02:54.373
Yo, Pops, H.F.D.
How about a game of hoops later?

02:54.541 --> 02:57.510
- You got it. Bring your A game.
- It's gonna be epic.

02:58.444 --> 03:00.344
I made you a remote-control caddy.

03:00.513 --> 03:04.745
Mom got all the supplies from the store
and then stayed up late to put it together.

03:04.918 --> 03:08.217
- But it was your idea.
- Wow.

03:08.388 --> 03:12.051
Okay, let's let your father enjoy
his breakfast and read his paper in peace.

03:12.225 --> 03:13.590
It's his day.

03:13.760 --> 03:16.251
- We love you, Dad.
- We love you, Dad.

03:19.799 --> 03:21.733
<i>FRANKIE:
My Mother's Day was right on course.</i>

03:21.901 --> 03:25.632
<i>I had choked down some runny eggs,
burnt waffle and old fried bologna.</i>

03:26.206 --> 03:29.107
<i>Who would've thought old bologna
would be the star of that show?</i>

03:29.275 --> 03:31.641
Ahh, this is torture. Turn it down.

03:34.247 --> 03:37.239
Mom, do you like your breakfast?
You haven't eaten very much.

03:37.417 --> 03:39.783
Yes, I did. When you weren't looking.

03:39.953 --> 03:43.616
And you know, Grandma's coming later
for our lunch at Neptune's Grill.

03:43.790 --> 03:47.521
I have to save room for the peach pie.
It's my favorite.

03:49.028 --> 03:51.724
Hey, Mike,
can you bring me the stain remover?

03:51.898 --> 03:55.857
MIKE: Don't know where it is.
- Yes, you do. It's under the sink.

03:56.035 --> 03:58.697
MIKE: I see dishwashing soap.
- Next to that.

03:58.871 --> 04:03.035
MIKE: Yeah, we must be out of it.
- No, no. Move stuff around.

04:03.209 --> 04:04.676
Are you moving stuff around?

04:07.914 --> 04:09.745
- This it?
- That's drain cleaner.

04:09.916 --> 04:11.747
So you can't use it?

04:11.918 --> 04:15.479
I'll get it later. Right now I gotta shower.

04:15.655 --> 04:20.024
Well, thank you for the most wonderful
Mother's Day breakfast.

04:20.192 --> 04:22.753
I think this was my best one yet.

04:22.929 --> 04:26.023
And when I get out,
I'll open the rest of my presents.

04:26.199 --> 04:27.632
Take your time.

04:28.401 --> 04:30.028
It's your day.

04:30.203 --> 04:31.261
Grab the coupon drawer.

04:31.437 --> 04:35.396
We got 20 minutes to hit the drugstore
and get your mom something she'll treasure.

04:39.279 --> 04:42.840
<i>FRANKIE: I could tell by the look in
his eyes Mike forgot to get me a gift.</i>

04:43.016 --> 04:45.280
<i>So I decided
to take an extra-long shower.</i>

04:45.451 --> 04:48.011
<i>I thought I'd give them time
to find me something nice.</i>

04:48.855 --> 04:51.847
Didn't we just do Valentine's Day?
This whole thing's a racket.

04:52.025 --> 04:55.586
They trump up these phony holidays
just so they can sell you a bunch of crap.

04:55.762 --> 04:57.821
If we had any guts,
we'd just say no to this.

04:57.997 --> 05:01.865
That'd be the best gift I could give Mom,
to teach you kids some backbone.

05:03.136 --> 05:04.797
All right, let's find that gift.

05:08.274 --> 05:11.402
Ugh, got up too early. Must get sleep.

05:11.577 --> 05:14.171
Yay, chair.

05:15.014 --> 05:16.606
[SIGHS]

05:23.856 --> 05:25.551
Hey, Mike.

05:25.725 --> 05:28.694
- Bob.
- You forgot Mother's Day, didn't you?

05:28.861 --> 05:32.319
Well, you know, they trump up
these holidays and they expect peop...

05:32.498 --> 05:34.864
- Forget it.
- Mike, let me help, okay?

05:35.301 --> 05:37.292
<i>MAN [ON PA]:
Manager to the pharmacy counter.</i>

05:37.470 --> 05:39.995
Oh, these are great.
You can record your own message.

05:40.173 --> 05:41.697
You can do accents, anything you want.

05:41.874 --> 05:44.434
[IN BRITISH ACCENT]
Hello, hello. Happy Mom's Day, Frankie.

05:44.610 --> 05:45.634
[LAUGHS]

05:45.812 --> 05:48.440
- Yeah, okay. I'm in kind of a hurry here.
BRICK: Hey, Dad?

05:48.614 --> 05:51.139
Would Mom like something
called "condoms"?

05:51.317 --> 05:55.413
- Does she like pleasure?
- No. Get out of that aisle.

05:55.588 --> 05:58.148
Dad, look. We have to get this for Mom.

06:00.593 --> 06:03.858
"Think of the thing you
cannot do and then do it."

06:04.030 --> 06:06.555
- That is so powerful.
- I know.

06:06.733 --> 06:08.598
No. We got plenty of fridge magnets.

06:08.768 --> 06:12.033
From the sewer-rooter people,
the pizza-delivery guy.

06:12.205 --> 06:14.935
<i>WOMAN [ON PA]:
Mrs. Travinski to the pharmacy for pickup.</i>

06:15.108 --> 06:18.202
Hey, this is that stain remover
Mom was talking about earlier.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.573
We know she wants it.

06:21.981 --> 06:26.042
Okay, I know you said you wouldn't get it
for Mom, but what if you got it for me?

06:26.219 --> 06:28.949
- No.
- But, Dad, please?

06:29.122 --> 06:31.352
I just love it so much.

06:31.524 --> 06:34.789
Sue, I'm not spending $5
on a magnet we don't need.

06:35.728 --> 06:37.195
We got a gift for Mom.

06:38.197 --> 06:41.223
What is with you kids?
Stop goofing around and get serious.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.425
Your mom works hard...

06:42.602 --> 06:45.537
...and she deserves a nice gift
that shows her how much we care.

06:47.707 --> 06:49.902
We thought of wrapping it
but then didn't.

06:50.076 --> 06:53.068
Who needs wrapping?
Just takes longer to get to the present.

06:57.216 --> 06:59.582
An inflatable foot bath.

07:00.219 --> 07:02.244
Wow!

07:02.422 --> 07:03.582
Wow.

07:03.756 --> 07:05.519
You're always saying your feet hurt...

07:05.691 --> 07:08.387
...and it's inflatable,
so you can take it when you travel.

07:08.561 --> 07:11.291
It's got sloughing bumps
to remove dead skin.

07:11.898 --> 07:14.298
[WHISPERS]
Sloughing bumps.

07:16.402 --> 07:20.099
<i>FRANKIE: And this is what Mike got
for Father's Day last year:</i>

07:20.273 --> 07:22.002
Oh, my God.

07:22.175 --> 07:24.109
No way.

07:24.277 --> 07:25.574
- Is this?
- Yep.

07:25.745 --> 07:29.112
A certified piece of IU Hoosier gym.

07:29.282 --> 07:32.513
Remember we read that they were
replacing the floor in Assembly Hall?

07:32.685 --> 07:36.451
Well, I called the campus to see
if we could buy a piece of the old floor...

07:36.622 --> 07:40.388
...and they gave me like a zillion numbers,
but I tracked down the right guy...

07:40.560 --> 07:44.496
...and he told me he would sell me a piece
but I had to come get it that morning.

07:44.664 --> 07:47.360
So I drove in this snowstorm
to Bloomington...

07:47.533 --> 07:50.331
...and I swear
I had like almost two crashes...

07:50.503 --> 07:53.666
...but it was so worth it
just to see this look on your face.

07:53.840 --> 07:57.776
Wow. I can't believe you thought of this.

07:58.644 --> 08:00.202
Wow.

08:00.379 --> 08:02.313
I can't believe you thought of this.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.212
All right, I'm gonna leave you alone.
It's your day.

08:06.586 --> 08:11.182
<i>Okay, I'm gonna just relax
and read my People magazine.</i>

08:11.357 --> 08:13.689
Also, while we were at the drugstore,
I got glue...

08:13.860 --> 08:16.226
...so now I can fix your picture frame.

08:17.797 --> 08:22.894
Brick, what kind of pasta do you want
at the top of my frame, elbow or farfalle?

08:23.503 --> 08:26.063
Whatever you want. It's your day.

08:27.740 --> 08:31.232
And if you can find a picture of yourself
to put in it, that'd be good too.

08:32.645 --> 08:34.977
<i>FRANKIE: And this is what Mike was doing
on Father's Day:</i>

08:35.147 --> 08:36.171
<i>MAN [ON TV]:
Great defense.</i>

08:36.349 --> 08:40.217
<i>And the stadium went nuts tonight, folks.
The Bearcats came in and took one home.</i>

08:42.121 --> 08:43.712
[PHONE RINGING]

08:44.222 --> 08:45.315
Somebody get that.

08:47.793 --> 08:52.230
Hello? Anybody?
Somebody I was just talking to, maybe?

08:55.301 --> 08:56.666
[SIGHS]

08:56.836 --> 08:58.633
Hello?

08:59.972 --> 09:01.564
Hi, Mom.

09:01.741 --> 09:05.233
Okay. Change of plans.
I'm going to Grandma's.

09:05.411 --> 09:07.538
What? Why? She always comes here.

09:07.713 --> 09:10.978
Yeah, well, Dad had to go to the shop
because of some possum problem...

09:11.150 --> 09:15.883
...and since her sciatica's been acting up,
Mom can't feel her feet, so she can't drive.

09:16.055 --> 09:18.114
I don't want her to be alone
on Mother's Day.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.885
I'm gonna have to just drive up
and surprise her.

09:21.060 --> 09:23.221
Oh, my God,
this conversation is so boring...

09:23.396 --> 09:25.864
...yet just loud enough
that I can't sleep through it.

09:26.032 --> 09:28.933
All right. I'll try to switch
our lunch reservations to dinner.

09:29.101 --> 09:31.865
Oh, good.
That way I still get my peach pie.

09:32.038 --> 09:33.835
"The Octomom is looking forward...

09:34.006 --> 09:36.770
...to a nice brunch at home."
- Ah.

09:36.943 --> 09:41.778
- Mom, can I come with you to Grandma's?
- Oh, thank you, Sue. That'll be fun.

09:41.948 --> 09:43.779
A mother-daughter trip on Mother's Day.

09:43.950 --> 09:46.077
The whole way,
we'll listen to music and gab.

09:51.157 --> 09:54.320
- So you wanna listen to some music?
- No.

09:55.261 --> 09:57.855
- You wanna talk?
- No.

09:58.264 --> 10:02.257
Sue, no offense, but if I wanted to ride
in silence, I would've brought your dad.

10:02.435 --> 10:04.460
What's going on with you?

10:08.307 --> 10:10.605
Honey, what's the matter?

10:11.077 --> 10:12.271
Never mind.

10:12.979 --> 10:16.779
Sue, something is obviously wrong.
Now tell me.

10:17.583 --> 10:21.576
- It'll ruin your Mother's Day.
- Nothing you can say would do that.

10:21.754 --> 10:25.918
<i>FRANKIE: I already got a foot bath.
Ship's pretty much sailed on that one.</i>

10:26.092 --> 10:29.186
- I broke a commandment.
- Oh.

10:29.362 --> 10:31.023
Okay.

10:31.530 --> 10:34.328
- Which one?
- I stole something.

10:34.500 --> 10:38.197
- I stole an inspirational fridge magnet.
- A what?

10:38.371 --> 10:41.898
A magnet for the fridge,
to hold papers and stuff.

10:42.074 --> 10:44.406
I just loved it so much,
and Dad wouldn't buy it...

10:44.577 --> 10:45.839
...and now I feel terrible.

10:46.012 --> 10:48.674
I never thought I would be
the kind of person to steal...

10:48.848 --> 10:53.012
...but the magnet said "Think of the
thing you cannot do and then do it."

10:53.185 --> 10:55.346
So I thought about it and then I did it.

10:55.521 --> 11:00.458
Oh, my God. I'm a stealer. I stole.

11:00.726 --> 11:02.660
[RETCHES]

11:02.828 --> 11:06.025
Sue. Honey.

11:07.900 --> 11:11.267
See? See, it's got a dolphin.

11:11.437 --> 11:13.496
And a kite.

11:14.206 --> 11:15.867
[VOMITS]

11:17.643 --> 11:21.135
It'll be okay, honey.
Clearly, you know what you did was wrong.

11:21.313 --> 11:24.077
We'll take it back to the store
and explain what happened...

11:24.250 --> 11:26.878
...and you can apologize.

11:27.053 --> 11:28.918
<i>FRANKIE:
And about this time on Father's Day...</i>

11:31.857 --> 11:33.916
<i>You know what?
I'm not even gonna go there.</i>

11:34.093 --> 11:36.391
<i>It's just gonna make me mad.</i>

11:40.032 --> 11:42.159
<i>FRANKIE: After stopping at
a do-it-yourself car wash...</i>

11:42.334 --> 11:44.165
<i>...and hosing down the car and Sue...</i>

11:44.336 --> 11:45.997
<i>...we finally made it to Grandma's house.</i>

11:46.172 --> 11:48.163
<i>[ON RADIO]
A true-blue spectacle</i>

11:48.374 --> 11:51.036
<i>A miracle come true</i>

11:51.410 --> 11:53.401
<i>We're together, baby</i>

11:53.579 --> 11:55.979
<i>I was goin' crazy
Till the...</i>

11:56.148 --> 11:58.116
Oh, my gosh.

11:59.118 --> 12:00.983
Hey, Mom.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.155
What are you girls doing here?

12:04.590 --> 12:07.457
We thought we'd come up and surprise you.
Looks like we did.

12:07.626 --> 12:11.153
Oh, you know, just frosting my hair,
frying a steak...

12:11.330 --> 12:13.798
...and having a little glass of white zin.

12:13.966 --> 12:15.365
Okay, two glasses. You got me.

12:15.534 --> 12:16.728
[BOTH LAUGH]

12:16.902 --> 12:20.702
Oh, well, you were looking good out there.
Your leg must be feeling better.

12:20.873 --> 12:23.842
Well, you know how sciatica is.
It comes and goes.

12:24.343 --> 12:29.007
It helps to move around, and nobody
gets me going like Barry. Ha, ha.

12:29.181 --> 12:32.048
Oh, look at you, Chop Suey.

12:32.218 --> 12:35.483
Oh, stop growing so fast
and making me feel old.

12:35.654 --> 12:37.849
- Happy Mother's Day, Grandma.
- Thank you, sugar.

12:38.023 --> 12:40.423
But you didn't have to come all this way.

12:40.593 --> 12:42.117
- My gosh.
- Are you kidding?

12:42.294 --> 12:45.161
We couldn't let you be alone
on Mother's Day.

12:45.331 --> 12:49.324
Oh! Oh, you nut. Oh.

12:49.502 --> 12:52.665
Why did you do this?

12:53.506 --> 12:54.734
Ah.

12:57.443 --> 13:00.276
Oh, my.

13:00.446 --> 13:03.540
Look at this.

13:03.716 --> 13:05.741
A food dehydrator.

13:05.918 --> 13:08.648
Well, I know how much
you love dried apricots and raisins.

13:08.821 --> 13:12.120
So now you can buy apricots and grapes,
make your own.

13:12.291 --> 13:15.124
Oh, boy. And it's so big.

13:15.628 --> 13:18.961
Why don't I go make room for this
in the kitchen?

13:19.131 --> 13:22.396
Come on, Chop Suey.
You can help yourself to the candy drawer.

13:22.568 --> 13:26.868
Your grandpa's blood sugar's out of whack,
so there's still some good stuff in there.

13:27.039 --> 13:31.032
I don't deserve a treat.
I stole an inspirational fridge magnet.

13:31.911 --> 13:33.105
<i>[MOUTHS]
I'll call you.</i>

13:33.279 --> 13:34.906
Oh.

13:35.080 --> 13:39.483
Honey, we all do stupid things,
but we all deserve chocolate.

13:40.085 --> 13:42.451
Come with Grandma.
Let's talk about what happened.

13:47.126 --> 13:51.620
Oh, yeah, baby.
That's what I'm talking about.

13:51.797 --> 13:55.563
<i>FRANKIE: So while a real mom with
more experience than me was fixing Sue...</i>

13:55.734 --> 13:57.793
<i>...I could finally catch a break.</i>

13:57.970 --> 14:01.997
<i>What is it about being at your mom's house
that lets you completely relax?</i>

14:06.545 --> 14:08.137
Mm.

14:10.482 --> 14:12.382
[SIGHS]

14:12.551 --> 14:16.419
Hey, Mom, I'm thirsty.
Can you bring me a pop or something?

14:21.227 --> 14:23.491
Thank you. Oh!

14:23.662 --> 14:24.788
Your hair looks nice.

14:24.964 --> 14:29.128
Oh, yeah? Sue helped me finish it off.
It's not too frosted?

14:29.301 --> 14:32.099
No, no, in a couple weeks,
it'll be perfect.

14:32.938 --> 14:34.098
[YAWNS]

14:34.273 --> 14:37.970
How long was I asleep? I'm starving.

14:38.143 --> 14:40.703
Hey, you know what would be great?

14:40.880 --> 14:44.976
One of your grilled cheese sandwiches
with the potato chips in the middle.

14:45.651 --> 14:47.812
- I love the way you make them.
- Uh, okay.

14:47.987 --> 14:51.548
<i>Could you not lean on my People?
You're making it all crinkly.</i>

14:51.724 --> 14:53.385
Sorry.

14:55.127 --> 14:59.621
- And, Mom, in triangles, okay?
- I know, triangles.

15:01.767 --> 15:05.225
How do you guys survive
with just basic cable?

15:06.105 --> 15:07.402
Mm!

15:07.573 --> 15:09.040
Thanks, Mom.

15:09.208 --> 15:11.938
Ooh, this looks good.

15:13.012 --> 15:14.411
Aww!

15:14.580 --> 15:16.548
No chips?

15:17.850 --> 15:22.048
Hey, how long do you think it would take
to make some pudding? Hmm?

15:27.893 --> 15:30.259
- Are you mad?
- No.

15:30.429 --> 15:32.727
Anything else I can get you
on Mother's Day?

15:32.898 --> 15:34.889
See, now you sound mad.

15:35.067 --> 15:37.558
I came here so you wouldn't be alone
on Mother's Day.

15:37.736 --> 15:42.002
Well, I'm sorry, but did you ever think
maybe I wanted to be alone?

15:43.175 --> 15:45.541
You didn't wanna be with your daughter
on Mother's Day?

15:45.711 --> 15:48.179
- Oh, I didn't say that.
- Yeah, you did, Mom.

15:48.347 --> 15:49.371
You said exactly that.

15:49.548 --> 15:52.676
You said, "Sorry, but did you ever think
I wanted to be alone?"

15:52.851 --> 15:54.284
What are you, a court reporter?

15:54.453 --> 15:58.321
I'm sorry if I drove an hour and a half
to be with my mother on Mother's Day.

15:58.490 --> 16:02.085
I had no idea it would be an inconvenience.
I thought it would make you happy.

16:02.261 --> 16:06.095
Frankie, I am never alone in this house.

16:06.265 --> 16:09.723
Your dad is always here,
asking me about this, asking me about that.

16:09.902 --> 16:12.302
"Can I eat this? Where's my raincoat?"

16:12.471 --> 16:14.462
Now he's out with his possums...

16:14.640 --> 16:17.575
...and I just wanted a minute
to frost my damn hair...

16:17.743 --> 16:20.769
...and drink my damn wine
and listen to my damn music...

16:20.946 --> 16:22.846
...without getting anyone anything...

16:23.015 --> 16:26.041
...or making anybody
any grilled cheese sandwiches...

16:26.218 --> 16:28.049
...with potato chips in the middle.

16:28.554 --> 16:29.953
Oh, my God.

16:30.122 --> 16:32.454
I'll bet your sciatic nerve
isn't really acting up.

16:32.624 --> 16:35.252
I'll bet you made that up
as an excuse to not see me.

16:35.427 --> 16:38.988
Oh, come on, you know how sciatica is.
It comes and goes.

16:39.164 --> 16:40.426
Oh, I don't know.

16:40.599 --> 16:43.159
You were boogying down pretty hard there,
Lady Flash.

16:43.335 --> 16:46.566
It comes and goes.

16:46.739 --> 16:49.606
Forget it, just forget it.
I don't expect you to understand.

16:50.242 --> 16:52.472
I don't understand?

16:52.644 --> 16:55.238
You think I wouldn't wanna have a house
all to myself?

16:55.414 --> 16:58.178
You think I wouldn't love
to be alone on Mother's Day...

16:58.350 --> 17:00.511
...sucking down a glass
of white zinfandel?

17:00.686 --> 17:03.120
You don't wanna be with your daughter
on Mother's Day?

17:03.288 --> 17:07.190
- Sue, I didn't say that.
- Yes, you did. You said exactly that.

17:07.358 --> 17:09.452
- Sue, come on.
- Well, I'm sorry.

17:09.627 --> 17:12.790
If you guys wanted to be alone,
why didn't you just say so?

17:12.964 --> 17:14.090
PAT:
It's really hard, Sue.

17:14.266 --> 17:17.030
It's really hard to say you don't wanna
be with your family.

17:17.202 --> 17:20.637
It's really hard to say
you don't wanna dry your own fruit.

17:20.806 --> 17:24.435
- You didn't like your dehydrator?
- It's ridiculous.

17:24.609 --> 17:26.669
I'm gonna go buy $4-a-pound grapes...

17:26.845 --> 17:30.406
...and spend hours turning them
into 99-cent raisins?

17:30.582 --> 17:31.606
Use your head.

17:31.784 --> 17:35.481
You think that's a horrible gift?
I got an inflatable foot bath.

17:35.654 --> 17:38.885
- You don't like your foot bath?
- It's ridiculous.

17:39.058 --> 17:42.152
What about me says I'm the kind
that wants to blow something up...

17:42.327 --> 17:43.851
...and stick my feet in it?

