17:54.573 --> 17:57.133
<i>FRANKIE: It took three hours
and two trips to the candy drawer...</i>

17:57.309 --> 17:59.209
<i>...to undo everything that had been said.</i>

17:59.378 --> 18:03.337
I don't want us to be fighting
on Mother's Day.

18:03.515 --> 18:06.678
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- I know, honey.

18:06.852 --> 18:09.912
- I'm sorry, Sue.
- I know, Mom.

18:10.089 --> 18:11.989
Oh!

18:16.228 --> 18:17.593
<i>FRANKIE:
By the time we were done...</i>

18:17.763 --> 18:20.061
<i>...there was no way
I was making it for Neptune's Grill...</i>

18:20.232 --> 18:23.099
<i>...so I told Mike and the boys
to bring me back peach pie.</i>

18:23.268 --> 18:24.599
<i>And my Mother's Day dinner?</i>

18:24.770 --> 18:28.399
I'll have a number seven with double-fried
dark meat and monster fries...

18:28.574 --> 18:32.510
...a number four with extreme cheese tots,
and two diet root beers.

18:32.678 --> 18:34.612
<i>FRANKIE:
And as for Mike's Father's Day dinner...</i>

18:34.780 --> 18:36.304
Here it is, your favorite dinner.

18:36.482 --> 18:39.747
Steak and a mashed-potato Dad
with bacon arms.

18:40.719 --> 18:43.017
[ALL LAUGHING]

18:43.755 --> 18:45.723
<i>GIRL:
Pull around.</i>

18:48.460 --> 18:51.623
Hey, everybody. We're back.

18:54.299 --> 18:56.267
Oh, come on.

19:01.673 --> 19:04.005
Aw, Brick.

19:08.647 --> 19:10.672
Oh, come on.

19:12.117 --> 19:14.347
Hey, you're back. How's your mom?

19:14.520 --> 19:17.318
Good. How was my Mother's Day dinner?

19:17.489 --> 19:19.719
Not bad.
The waitress thought I was a widower.

19:19.892 --> 19:22.019
She gave us free shrimp balls.

19:22.594 --> 19:24.084
- So?
- What?

19:24.263 --> 19:25.594
My pie?

19:26.698 --> 19:28.962
I'm going back. I'm going back right now.

19:29.134 --> 19:31.967
- Sweet, get me more shrimp balls.
- Oh, forget it.

19:35.507 --> 19:38.635
<i>FRANKIE:
Some days, from start to finish, just blow.</i>

19:38.810 --> 19:41.574
I'm never doing that again.

19:41.747 --> 19:43.180
What?

19:43.348 --> 19:45.714
- Mother's Day?
- Yeah, Mother's Day.

19:45.884 --> 19:49.342
- It should be outlawed.
- What? You don't mean that.

19:49.521 --> 19:52.786
The kids made you breakfast.
You went to see your mom. It was good.

19:52.958 --> 19:55.153
You're confusing Mother's Day
with Father's Day.

19:55.327 --> 19:58.125
Father's day is great. Know why?
Because a mom is running it.

19:58.297 --> 20:01.232
You know what you need? A foot bath.

20:01.400 --> 20:03.800
I'm gonna blow you up a foot bath.

20:09.775 --> 20:13.404
I'll tell you one thing,
I'm never having kids.

20:13.579 --> 20:16.241
What? Why would you say that?

20:16.415 --> 20:18.542
Ugh, it just seems hard.

20:18.717 --> 20:22.483
I couldn't handle it the way you do.
You're good at it.

20:22.654 --> 20:25.145
See, now,
that's why you'll love having kids.

20:25.324 --> 20:27.053
Same reason I do.

20:27.226 --> 20:30.457
Because after a rough day,
one of them will come in, give you a hug...

20:30.629 --> 20:32.756
...and say something like that.

20:33.665 --> 20:35.565
But aren't we the cause of the rough day?

20:36.435 --> 20:38.562
Well, you can't overthink it.

20:38.737 --> 20:40.102
We cleaned up the kitchen.

20:40.505 --> 20:42.735
Oh, see?

20:42.908 --> 20:46.036
That was exhausting. I'm beat.

20:48.080 --> 20:49.980
Come on.

20:51.617 --> 20:53.175
Ah.

20:53.385 --> 20:54.409
I'll get it.

20:54.586 --> 20:57.419
I just gotta poke a tweezer
in the valve to open it up.

20:59.391 --> 21:02.849
- Where are the tweezers?
- Move stuff around.

21:03.028 --> 21:06.122
<i>FRANKIE: Mike's right.
Mother's Day is sort of a made-up holiday.</i>

21:06.298 --> 21:08.061
<i>It doesn't always live up to the hype.</i>

21:08.233 --> 21:10.326
<i>That's what led me
to create a new holiday...</i>

21:10.502 --> 21:12.902
<i>...one that's turned out
to be one of my favorites.</i>

21:14.239 --> 21:17.208
<i>I call it The Day After Mother's Day.</i>

21:17.376 --> 21:20.777
- Can I get you anything else?
- No, I'm so good.

21:21.446 --> 21:22.970
<i>FRANKIE:
Mother's Day is for them.</i>

21:23.148 --> 21:26.140
<i>The Day After Mother's Day is for me.</i>

21:26.551 --> 21:29.714
<i>It's kind of like Father's Day for mothers.</i>

